1001923.animalDescription:
Addie is a 16 month old, purebred Pembroke Welsh Corgi! Addie enjoys playing frisbee or catch with anything! Although she is content being independent while enjoying a chew bone or favorite toy, she does crave attention. She enjoys going for walks, however, with her short legs, she does tire out and then enjoys a nice nap!


For more information please fill out APPLICATION


Our Pets can be seen upon appointment or in person every Saturday.


Please visit our EVENTS PAGE for more information on our time and locations.


Pets listed in TARA's web site are eligible to a two week trial.


Adoption fee varies, usually from $150.00.00 to $250.00.


For more information, please visit our Web Site.

1004555.animalDescription:
Kathryn is a 4yr old spayed female 35 lb Corgi mix. She is a sweetie, a major lovebug and good with everyone. Kathryn is very goofy, and is pretty sure she is a 'lap dog' as she loves to climb up, and snuggle if allowed.

Kathryn is crate trained, housetrained,and rides well in the car. Kathryn knows 'sit', and has learned new manners because she is very treat motivated. She is happy to learn new things for a treat!  Kathryn does not care for other animals in the home although she is fine with meeting them when out & about.

Kathyrn likes to go for walks but isn't too active, and will play when the mood strikes her. She is SUCH a sweet and fun dog she will make a great companion for someone!

1005564.animalDescription:
Angel is a spayed, female about 5 years old. She is crate trained and working on her house training. Angel has a sweet personality, although a little shy. She was an outdoor only dog most of her life and is just learning to enjoy the pleasures of sleeping at your feet indoors. She loves children, is good with other dogs and with cats. She has a quiet nature, and will simply place her paw in your hand or on your leg when she is requesting attention. Easy to please and grateful for a loving home, given the time she needs to develop her self-esteem, Angel will make a wonderful, loving companion. She would fit into a quiet home with an elderly couple or into a home with children and other pets. Angel is looking for a place to CALL HER OWN, where she can live happily ever after.

Angel's adoption fee is $50.00. She is spayed and has received all age appropriate vaccinations.

For details on how to adopt one of our perfect pets, adoption fees, adoption clinic schedules and special events just click on our group name (Pick of the Pound) on the right hand side of this page.
